SENATE RESOLUTION 326
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Tarius Johnson upon
his induction into the Jackson-Madison County
Sports Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this legislative body pay tribute to those gifted athletes,
coaches, and administrators who have attained the very pinnacle of sporting achievement; and
WHEREAS, Tarius Johnson is one such legendary athlete, who is being inducted into
the Jackson-Madison County Sports Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, an iconic graduate of Liberty High School, Mr. Johnson is one of the best
football players in Jackson-Madison County history; and
WHEREAS, Tarius Johnson was an important contributor to two TSSAA Class 3-A state
football championship teams during his career at Liberty; and
WHEREAS, he later won an Ohio Valley Conference football championship while playing
for Eastern Kentucky University; and
WHEREAS, Tarius Johnson is now in his second year of teaching at Chester County
High School, where he provides adroit leadership as head coach of the boys' basketball team
and oversees the school's Eagle Academy; and
WHEREAS, Coach Johnson plays an important role in developing student athletes both
on the court and in the classroom, working with purpose and conviction to help his charges grow
into their roles as the informed citizens and civic leaders of tomorrow; and
WHEREAS, Tarius Johnson has demonstrated leadership, skill, and dedication
throughout his athletic career and during his tenure as a teacher and coach, and it is fitting that
we should honor him on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and congratulate
